crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. A small slender-stemmed palm, about 15 feet high, with pinnate leaves. Native to Brazil. For previous introduction see 104681.

crops.presented_by: Robert M. Grey, Superintendent, Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.institution_involved: Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. A small shrub with drooping branches and rounded leaves, the two lobes rounded oval, white-hairy beneath. The small yellow flowers are in racemes of 12 to 18. Native to eastern India.

crops.presented_by: Robert M. Grey, Superintendent, Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.institution_involved: Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. A palm, native to China, with a short thick trunk up to 6 feet high and 1 foot thick, having a crown of reniform palmately divided leaves 4 to 6 feet across on petioles about 5 feet long, which are armed below the middle with recurved brown spines more than an inch long. For previous introduction see 93412.

crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. A slender palm about 50 feet high, with a crown of large fan-shaped leaves. It is native to Malacca. For previous introduction see 104240.

crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. A large tropical tree, 40 to 60 feet high, with compound leaves a foot or less in length, the two to four broadly elliptic leaves being 2 to 4 inches long. The white flowers are in small corymbs. Native to southern India.

crops.presented_by: Robert M. Grey, Superintendent, Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.institution_involved: Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. Plants of a tropical tree of moderate size, with ovate or rounded thick leaves 5 or 6 inches long and fragrant white flowers, 2 inches long, in corymblike clusters. Native to Assam, India.

crops.presented_by: Robert M. Grey, Superintendent, Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.institution_involved: Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.description: Seeds and plants from Cuba. An evergreen tree with alternate pinnate leaves and racemes of purplish pea-like flowers. For previous introduction see 94776.

crops.origin: Central Mercedita, Pinar del Rio, Cuba
crops.presented_by: through W. A. Mace, Madruga, Cuba, and L. H. Dewey, Bureau of Plant Industry
crops.institution_involved: Bureau of Plant Industry
crops.description: A tree, native to the East Indies, 30 to 40 feet high, with viscid milky juice and leathery ovate leaves 3 feet long, entire at the base but divided above into 3 to 9 lobes. The large fruits, 4 to 6 inches in diameter, are often seedless, but in this variety the seeds are present and are much the size, shape, and flavor of chestnuts. For previous introduction see 80173.

crops.presented_by: Julius Matz, Bureau of Plant Industry
crops.institution_involved: Bureau of Plant Industry
crops.description: Variety Zorzalena. A relatively tender variety. The tree is leafy, compact, and a good early bearer whose fruit is grown for its oil.

crops.description: A Colombian tree up to 100 feet high with a large thick trunk, smooth pale bark, large shallowly five- to seven-lobed leaves, and red flowers 1 inch long. The soft coarse pithlike wood is white or yellowish and is used for making canoes and rafts. For previous introduction see 98928.
